review_blob: Rich amber color, creamy, persistent head. Low carbonation and slightly syrupy feel. Tamed hoppy flavors, not as sharp as the 60.
Must try if found, great for sharing, sipped from a wine glass. Taste is thick and malty, almost syrupy
Smokey and chocolatey. Mouthfeel is a little sharp but softens. Smooth finish to the bottom of the bottle.
Good overall flavour but the palate and after taste starts out rough. Builds on itself; the second pint is much better than the first.
beer_name: Third Street Bitter Neighbor Black IPA
